    <bioghist>Winthrop Sears, Jr., was an archivist at Henry Ford Museum and Greenfield Village. His wife Doris worked at Gale Research in Detroit, Mich. They lived in Livonia, Mich., and were members of the Rosedale Gardens Presbyterian Church.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Papers relating to the Sears' activities in the Rosedale Gardens Presbyterian Church and other Livonia organizations, including Livonia Citizens for Better Human Relations, the League of Women Voters of Livonia, the Livonia Historical Society, Nottingham Woods Civic Association. The church materials include files on issues of censorship and prejudice in Livonia. The collection also includes a number of photos of the celebration of the Detroit Tigers' 1984 World Series win.</scopecontent>
